      h2 Welcome to Kno U Kno
      p #{homeText}
      p
        | Starting a business is a journey built from clear questions, small experiments, and steady learning. At Kno U Kno we aim to convert the big, intimidating tasks of launching and running a business into short, practical questions you can answer today. This short guide focuses on three pillars: how to start, how to manage, and how to handle money. When you start, focus on the problem you solve, the simplest offering you can build, and who will pay for it. For management, prioritize systems that capture customer feedback and make decisions repeatable—document processes and assign clear ownership. Regarding money, understand your cash flow: what money comes in, what goes out, and how long it takes to collect payment. Always plan for a small runway and build pricing that reflects value, not just cost. Legal structure, permits, and simple contracts are important early steps but don’t let them stop momentum—use practical templates and expert advice only where risk requires it. Testing assumptions with early customers, keeping fixed costs low, and iterating on a minimum viable product will get you further than waiting for perfect plans. Over time, invest in team, tools, and modest automation to scale processes that work. Our question sets and examples are designed to guide these choices one step at a time; answer, save, and revisit your answers as your business grows.
